00247 //-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
00248 // SplitInVector
00249 //-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
00250 // Returns false in case of failure.
00251 // Only one split character is allowed
00252 template<class T> bool SplitInVector(string str,string split,vector<T> &r,ios_base&(&b)(ios_base&)=dec)
00253 {
00254 
00255    r.clear();
00256    QString qstr(str.c_str());
00257    QStringList sl = qstr.split(QString(split.c_str()),QString::SkipEmptyParts);
00258    for(int i=0;i<sl.size();i++)
00259    {
00260       std::istringstream iss(sl[i].toStdString());
00261       T j;
00262       if( !((iss >> b >> j).fail()))
00263          r.push_back(j);
00264       else
00265          return false;
00266    }
00267    return true;
00268 }
